abstract: Israel and the Palestinian Authority (PA) have reached an agreement to end a five-month long trade dispute, officials said on Thursday.
snippet: Israel and the Palestinian Authority (PA) have reached an agreement to end a five-month long trade dispute, officials said on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM/RAMALLAH — Israel and the Palestinian Authority (PA) have reached an agreement to end a five-month long trade dispute, officials said on Thursday.
headline_main: Israel, Palestinian Authority Agree to End Trade Dispute: Officials
headline_print_headline: Israel, Palestinian Authority Agree to End Trade Dispute: Officials

abstract: In the wee hours of Jan. 8, Tehran retaliated over the U.S. killing of Iran’s most powerful general by bombarding the al-Asad air base in Iraq.
snippet: In the wee hours of Jan. 8, Tehran retaliated over the U.S. killing of Iran’s most powerful general by bombarding the al-Asad air base in Iraq.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - In the wee hours of Jan. 8, Tehran retaliated over the U.S. killing of Iran’s most powerful general by bombarding the al-Asad air base in Iraq.
headline_main: 'Hit With a Truck'-How Iran's Missiles Inflicted Brain Injury on U.S. Troops
headline_print_headline: 'Hit With a Truck'-How Iran's Missiles Inflicted Brain Injury on U.S. Troops

abstract: New restrictions have made it close to impossible to send cars from the state overseas, and a busy industry has ground to a halt.
snippet: New restrictions have made it close to impossible to send cars from the state overseas, and a busy industry has ground to a halt.
lead_paragraph: Several times a month, ships loaded with used cars leave ports around New York, bound for sale in the Caribbean, West Africa and the Middle East. It is a bustling business that starts with car dealerships and involves auction companies, exporters, freight carriers and shipping lines.

abstract: The sentencing played out amid extraordinary upheaval at the Justice Department and a virtual standoff between the president and the attorney general.
snippet: The sentencing played out amid extraordinary upheaval at the Justice Department and a virtual standoff between the president and the attorney general.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Roger J. Stone Jr., a longtime friend and adviser of President Trump, was sentenced Thursday to more than three years in prison in a politically fraught case that put the president at odds with his attorney general, stirred widespread consternation in the Justice Department and provoked the judge in the case to denounce pressure on the justice system.

abstract: Congress should transform the department into an independent agency untouched by the president’s whims.
snippet: Congress should transform the department into an independent agency untouched by the president’s whims.
lead_paragraph: In view of the intensifying controversy over the politicization of the Department of Justice under Attorney General William Barr and its potential weaponization at the hands of President Trump, it is worth reviving a proposal that has not been seriously discussed since the Watergate era: Congress should transform the Justice Department into an independent agency, legally immunized from the president’s day-to-day control.

abstract: I am convinced that the killing and the maiming must stop, the deputy leader of the Taliban writes.
snippet: I am convinced that the killing and the maiming must stop, the deputy leader of the Taliban writes.
lead_paragraph: When our representatives started negotiating with the United States in 2018, our confidence that the talks would yield results was close to zero. We did not trust American intentions after 18 years of war and several previous attempts at negotiation that had proved futile.
